{
  "texts": [
    "The psychogenerator dataset, which underpins the construction of our personality-aligned models, reflects a participant pool skewed toward younger users (median age 22) and individuals who actively engage with technology platforms like Facebook.",
    "Although convenient and indicative of certain contemporary linguistic trends, this sampling bias may underrepresent older individuals, non-English speakers, or populations with limited internet access.",
    "As a result, the personality expressions learned by the model may implicitly prioritize the linguistic styles and values of younger, technologically savvy demographics.",
    "Such demographic homogeneity potentially undermines the model's fairness and inclusivity, limiting its effectiveness and acceptability in cross-cultural or intergenerational contexts (Hovy and Spruit, 2016).",
    "In addition to demographic representativeness, safety and ethical compliance pose significant challenges."
  ]
}